      "node_id": "chunk:it_s_what_s_happenin_0",
      "passage_index": 17,
      "title": "It's What's Happenin'",
      "score": 0.08153724640874248,
      "text": "It's What's Happenin'\nIt's What's Happenin' (subtitled The Varitone Sound of Clark Terry) is an album by American jazz trumpeter Clark Terry featuring performances recorded in 1967 for the Impulse! label. Remastered in 2012 to commemorate the 50th anniversary of Impulse! Records, it was reissued together with Terry's only other record for the label as a solo leader, \"The Happy Horns of Clark Terry\".",
      "score_breakdown": {
        "dense": 0.049796522765349654,
        "graph": 0.05232060411398033,
        "fact": 0.2563531843573738
      }
    },
    {
      "node_id": "chunk:kinfolk_album_0",
      "passage_index": 10,
      "title": "Kinfolk (album)",
      "score": 0.08113906156317269,
      "text": "Kinfolk (album)\nKinfolk is the debut and only album by American rap duo Ali & Gipp, released on August 14, 2007, through Derrty Entertainment and Universal Records. The first single off the album was already released, called \"Go 'Head\" featuring Chocolate Tai. The second single is \"N da Paint\" featuring Nelly. The third single is \"Work Dat, Twerk Dat\" featuring Murphy Lee. The fourth and final single is \"Almost Made Ya\" featuring LeToya Luckett.",
      "score_breakdown": {
        "dense": 0.050409396826518856,
        "graph": 0.058534461921441704,
        "fact": 0.23902369821436534
      }
    },
